OL,3,CColin Smyth MSP understood to be
OL,4,Cfacing charges over camera in Holyrood
OL,5,Ctoilet
OL,7,FA Scottish Parliament spokesperson
OL,8,Fsaid: "Given the ongoing criminal
OL,9,Finvestigation, the SPCB (Scottish
OL,10,FParliamentary Corporate Bureau) took
OL,11,Fthe decision this evening to
OL,12,Fdeactivate Colin Smyth's parliamentary
OL,13,Fpass. We have informed all building
OL,14,Fusers at Holyrood."
OL,16,FIt is understood that the decision was
OL,17,Ftaken on Thursday evening by the MSPs
OL,18,Fwho make up the bureau.
